21:13.343 --> 21:16.728
So Jesus was perfect and he gave his life for us.

21:16.748 --> 21:22.056
So he could give his life for us as a sacrifice, a perfect sacrifice, but he didn't stay dead, right?

21:22.777 --> 21:28.846
He rose from the dead, proved that he was who he said he was and proved that he had victory over sin and death in the grave.

21:29.367 --> 21:31.570
So he could justify us.

21:32.130 --> 21:33.151
We can't do that.

21:33.471 --> 21:37.176
We can't live a perfect life down across, be right, raise ourselves from the dead.

21:37.216 --> 21:37.896
We can't do that.

21:38.657 --> 21:40.519
It's about trusting in what he's already done.

21:41.480 --> 21:50.130
The difference in Christianity and every other religion of the world can be summed up in two words, do versus done.

21:51.451 --> 22:01.202
Every other religion in the world from the beginning of time till now is about what you can do to please your God or gods.

22:03.970 --> 22:08.035
Christianity is about what Jesus has already done.

22:08.075 --> 22:19.607
That's why it is impossible for anyone else to know for sure about the afterlife because it's up to them.

22:20.689 --> 22:24.593
How will they know if they could do enough or they've done enough?

22:26.295 --> 22:30.640
But Jesus says that we can have life and have it to the full.

22:30.940 --> 22:32.882
We can know that we have eternal life.

22:33.442 --> 22:34.664
through faith in Him.

22:35.244 --> 22:36.286
So we can have peace.

22:36.326 --> 22:38.328
I know where I'm going.

22:38.769 --> 22:41.773
This life is hard, but I know where I'm going.

22:42.333 --> 22:49.963
If the worst happens to me, I know I'm okay because I have peace with God and my eternity is secure.

22:51.605 --> 22:56.111
Hebrews 11, 6 says it this way, without faith, it's impossible to please Him.

22:56.771 --> 23:01.938
For whoever would draw near to God must believe that He exists and that He rewards those who seek Him.

23:02.210 --> 23:06.155
Yes, he offers peace with all with whom he is pleased.

23:06.175 --> 23:08.879
What it takes to please God is what that verse says right there.

23:09.559 --> 23:09.880
Trust.

23:10.581 --> 23:10.941
Trusting.

23:11.121 --> 23:12.163
Trust of what he says is true.

23:12.203 --> 23:14.906
Trust in Christ for forgiveness.

23:15.387 --> 23:20.053
And that's how we can have be justified before God because he's already paid for the penalty.

23:21.034 --> 23:27.743
A second thing, not only do we find it by faith that is peace with God, we protect it by prayer.

23:28.644 --> 23:30.226
We protect our peace by prayer.

23:31.010 --> 23:50.676
You know, it is possible to have peace with God, that is to be a follower of Jesus, to be engaged in church activities and reading the Bible every day and praying and having, it is possible to be at peace with God and still be anxious.

23:50.976 --> 23:52.258
Can anyone identify with that?

23:54.941 --> 23:58.546
You know, I'm reading a book called The Anxious Generation.

23:59.458 --> 24:01.220
actually written by an atheist, which is interesting.

24:02.943 --> 24:03.303
Great book.

24:03.323 --> 24:04.225
I've just really started.

24:04.485 --> 24:07.209
I've heard the guy speak, so I wanted to get it and read it.

24:07.609 --> 24:13.397
But he talks about how there's an epidemic of anxiety among teenagers and young adults.

24:14.198 --> 24:19.446
Gen Z, mostly, or to the greatest extent, but also millennials as well.

24:20.547 --> 24:21.689
There's a lot of anxiety.

24:22.890 --> 24:23.371
It's real.

24:23.932 --> 24:25.514
I see it in ministry.

24:26.075 --> 24:27.016
I see it in families.

24:27.076 --> 24:28.338
I see it in young people.

24:29.154 --> 24:30.395
And it breaks my heart.

24:31.336 --> 24:32.518
It's real, it's hard.

24:35.601 --> 24:40.026
We can have peace with God, we can be justified with God, and we can have our eternity secure.

24:40.647 --> 24:43.009
But there's a life to live between now and then, right?

24:44.110 --> 24:46.373
And sometimes we experience anxiety.

24:47.814 --> 24:48.415
God knows that.

24:49.636 --> 24:58.386
And God gives us a solution, not a cure like this, but he gives us a practice that helps with that.

24:58.754 --> 25:00.756
And this is in Philippians 4, 6, and 7.

25:02.298 --> 25:03.859
Do not be anxious about, read this with me.

25:04.279 --> 25:19.955
Do not be anxious about anything, but in everything by prayer and supplication with thanksgiving, let your requests be made known to God, and the peace of God, which surpasses all understanding, will guard your hearts and minds in Christ Jesus.

25:20.436 --> 25:25.200
He says, pray with supplication, prayer and supplication, pray with supplication, supplication is request.

25:25.701 --> 25:26.962
So pray specifically,

25:28.226 --> 25:44.690
Uh, pray specifically for what you're feeling, for what, what's hurting, what your desires are, what, what your interest is, what, you know, pray specifically, confessing sins, whatever, you know, pray specifically, but also pray with gratitude, pray gratefully.

25:45.852 --> 25:48.616
There's something powerful about gratitude.

25:49.557 --> 25:50.338
Very powerful.

25:51.500 --> 25:55.826
When you're feeling down, if you will just stop,

25:57.346 --> 25:58.968
and thank God for three things.

26:01.190 --> 26:04.033
It may be 10 things, just thank God.

26:04.053 --> 26:09.900
Sometimes the reason that we're having anxiety is because of what's going on.

26:10.901 --> 26:21.393
All the bad stuff that's going on, whether it's an illness, whether it's a loss of a loved one, a loss of a relationship, loss of a job, bad things, tribulation, as Jesus said.

26:23.195 --> 26:26.258
And sometimes it's just the anticipation

26:27.138 --> 26:27.899
What could go wrong?

26:28.079 --> 26:29.321
Everything's going right right now.

26:29.841 --> 26:30.622
What could go wrong?

26:31.223 --> 26:33.666
What if he doesn't call me?

26:34.808 --> 26:37.151
He hasn't texted me all day.

26:37.791 --> 26:38.492
What's wrong?

26:39.153 --> 26:40.735
I don't see any post on social media.

26:43.298 --> 26:45.081
So there's anxiety about what could happen.

26:46.362 --> 26:55.634
But if we are grateful, it changes our perspective about how the world is happening to us and how we are living in the world.

26:56.386 --> 26:57.787
And that's why it's here.

26:58.328 --> 27:01.491
So, pray specifically, pray gratefully and do this consistently.

27:02.232 --> 27:03.232
You make this a habit.

27:04.574 --> 27:07.036
It begins to change your perspective.

27:07.156 --> 27:08.858
That's what this is about.

27:09.679 --> 27:11.981
So, we find peace with God through faith.

27:12.541 --> 27:13.903
We protect it by prayer.

27:14.263 --> 27:18.847
It has to be not just something you do once in a while, but something you do on a regular basis.

27:18.907 --> 27:20.629
It's like eating right or exercising.

27:20.649 --> 27:22.250
It's spiritual exercise.

27:22.871 --> 27:26.034
And the second and last thing is this, repair it by forgiveness.

27:26.466 --> 27:30.591
repair your peace by forgiveness.

27:31.912 --> 27:34.635
Unresolved conflict, no secret.

27:35.877 --> 27:37.478
It robs us of peace, right?

27:39.701 --> 27:54.898
I wonder, I wonder if in this Christmas season, there's some people in your life that you really don't want to be with, but you know they're going to be sitting at the table tomorrow or next weekend or

27:55.458 --> 27:56.579
Maybe they hear tonight.

27:56.619 --> 28:03.207
I don't know, you know, so And maybe if you get a mirror out and look up, you know, they feel the same way about you, right?

28:03.487 --> 28:14.018
So It's interesting that relationships are the best part of life And they can be the worst part of life, right?

28:15.340 --> 28:24.530
Let's be real At Christmas, we feel this even greater tension because We don't want it to be that way

28:24.834 --> 28:25.956
We know it's not right.

28:26.056 --> 28:29.621
We don't want it to be that way.

28:29.641 --> 28:36.991
Romans 12, the beginning of verse 18 says this, if it is possible, as far as it depends on you, live at peace with everyone.

28:37.973 --> 28:44.402
It doesn't say, if it's easy, live at peace with everyone.

28:44.882 --> 28:51.632
If it's easy, everybody be at peace, there'd be no shooting, there'd be no conflict in the world that was bad.

28:52.012 --> 28:53.234
Everybody would be happy.

28:53.730 --> 28:54.952
Don't worry, be happy.

28:55.032 --> 28:55.933
It's just not like that.

28:55.973 --> 28:57.375
That's not the real world.

28:58.336 --> 29:00.459
But if it is possible, sometimes it's hard.

29:01.360 --> 29:10.352
If it is possible as far as it depends on you, you can't be responsible for other people's responses, but you are responsible for owning yours.

29:12.135 --> 29:23.570
And he says, what we can do when they're not receiving that, when they're not accepting the peace that we're trying to offer,

29:24.066 --> 29:29.111
19, do not take revenge, my dear friends, but leave room for God's wrath.

29:29.131 --> 29:30.953
First written, it is mine to avenge.

29:31.433 --> 29:32.835
I'll repay, says the Lord.

29:33.596 --> 29:35.598
God says, look, I'm going to take care of them.

29:35.618 --> 29:36.519
I'm going to take care of this.

29:36.619 --> 29:37.760
You just leave it to me.

29:38.220 --> 29:43.746
On the contrary, if your enemy is hungry, feed him.

29:44.346 --> 29:46.288
If he's thirsty, give him something to drink.

29:47.009 --> 29:50.192
In doing this, you will heat burning coals on his head.

29:50.593 --> 29:51.954
Okay, we're going to come back to that.

29:52.322 --> 29:55.886
Do not be overcome by evil, but overcome evil with what?

29:57.088 --> 29:57.408
Yeah.

29:59.290 --> 30:00.371
Heat burning culture on this head.

30:01.092 --> 30:04.616
So this is not like home alone, you know, the scene.

30:06.399 --> 30:08.941
This is not like burn all the hair off his head.

30:09.462 --> 30:11.244
This is actually an interesting thing.

30:11.304 --> 30:17.271
It's kind of a, it's a contextual point that Paul was making in this time in the first century.

30:18.092 --> 30:19.634
There were no matches.

30:20.450 --> 30:22.152
