30:23.554 --> 30:28.259
So people once they got a fire burning would keep their coals and sometimes they would take them with them.

30:29.360 --> 30:41.875
So what he's saying is, even if the fire goes out of their house, you take some coals and give it to them so that they can keep burning coals on them so that they can start their fire up.

30:42.336 --> 30:43.377
Not so you can burn them with it.

30:43.417 --> 30:45.399
In other words, kill them with kindness, basically.

30:47.341 --> 30:47.922
Here's the deal.

30:49.058 --> 30:53.883
It takes two to reconcile a relationship, but it only takes you to forgive.

30:55.505 --> 30:57.187
You don't forgive because people deserve it.

30:59.830 --> 31:00.911
You don't earn forgiveness.

31:03.354 --> 31:05.416
It's not for takeness, it's forgiveness.

31:05.957 --> 31:07.759
You're not taking something from them before you give it.

31:08.880 --> 31:09.541
You have to give it.

31:10.542 --> 31:11.984
